Value Type Assignment

To be able to understand how value type variable work, we need to know and understand three facts.
	1. A variable is a name that refers to a location in computer memory where a value is stored.
	2. A value type variable stores a value of that type.
	3. An Assignment statement stores a value in a variable


All of this should be quite familiar. This is basically how we have treated all variables and data type up until now.
	1. A variable is a name that refers to a location in computer memory where a value is stored.
	2. A variable stores a value of its type.
	3. An assignment statement stores a value in variable.
	4. Evaluating a variable retrieves a copy of the value stored there.

